# The mobile/ app is a separate Expo/React Native project (built via EAS or
# Xcode, never Vercel) — its own node_modules and generated native ios/android
# directories can balloon into tens of thousands of files (CocoaPods, vendored
# frameworks) that blow past Vercel's upload file-count limit. Vercel's CLI
# doesn't pick up mobile/.gitignore (nested), so this needs to be explicit here.
mobile/
